posts.body: What cool shit has everyone found on Zeronet that they did not know existed already? Will this board take off or will it fade into obscurity?

Generally speaking I like anything that makes people think about their security and their online footprint. I think the more people start to become familiar with tools like Tor or even a VPN, it helps keep the internet free and open. I can't say there is too much here on Zeronet that I like specifically other than being completely decentralized. I applaud the effort to get this board running and functional and hope that users will stick around to add content that draw even more people here.
